stylometry: Bayes theorem is the probability that something will occur or happen based on evidence and information we have received, and the inverst of that probability.  It is important because it not only gives us one way of looking at things but it gives us the inverse or opposite and allows us to see the way different things will happen based on the evidence that one receives about the possibility that something is going to happen.  It allows us to kind of play the devils advocate to see if something is going to happen based on evidence, well what is going to happen if something else happens based on the evidence.  We determine the posterior probability by multiplying the past probability of an event happening by the likelihood of an event happening in the future.  We need these in order to make decisions for the future and to analyze what has happened in the past and help us with ways to change the outcomes in the future based on what has happened in the past.  If we want to see the posterior probability that a college graduate is going to buy a house we would take the past probability of a college graduate buying house (or the actual probability that happened in the past) and muliply that number by the likelihood or estimate that college graduates willl buy houses when they graduate in 2011.  This will give us the posterior probability for the current proposition of the real estate industry and whether to target college graduates or not.
